Detailed Description

cvmx_l2c_spar1

L2C_SPAR1 = L2 Set Partitioning Register (PP4-7)

Description: L2 Set Partitioning Register

Notes:

  • When a bit is set in the UMSK'x' register, a memory command issued from PP='x' will NOT select that set for replacement.
  • There should ALWAYS BE at least 1 bit clear in each UMSK'x' register for proper L2 cache operation
  • NOTES: When L2C FUSE[136] is blown(CRIP_1024K), then SETS#7-4 are SET in all UMSK'x' registers When L2C FUSE[137] is blown(CRIP_512K), then SETS#7-2 are SET in all UMSK'x' registers
